  "prompt": "What are the different types of circumcisions?",
  "response": "There are several types of circumcision procedures:\n\n1. Traditional/Religious Circumcision\n- Performed for cultural or religious reasons\n- Often done by religious leaders\n- Varies by specific cultural practices\n\n2. Medical Circumcision\n- Performed by healthcare professionals\n- Done for medical reasons or preventive health\n- Uses sterile medical techniques\n\n3. Surgical Techniques:\n- Dorsal Slit Method\n- Sleeve Resection\n- Forceps-Guided Method\n- Gomco Clamp Method\n- Plastibell Method\n\n4. Types by Extent of Foreskin Removal:\n- Low/Loose: Minimal skin removal\n- Medium: Moderate skin removal\n- High/Tight: Maximum skin removal\n\n5. Cosmetic Circumcision\n- Performed for aesthetic or personal preferences\n- Usually done in clinical settings\n\n6. Adult vs. Infant Circumcision\n- Different procedures and considerations based on age\n\nEach method has specific techniques, potential risks, and recovery processes. The choice depends on medical, cultural, and personal factors.",
